---
import Legal from "../layouts/Legal.astro";
import { GITHUB_URL } from "../lib/config";
---

<Legal
  title="Privacy — CLUB"
  description="How the CLUB project website handles visitor data. No cookies, no analytics, no telemetry."
  path="/privacy"
  ogImage="/og/privacy.png"
  eyebrow="Legal — Website privacy"
  heading="Privacy on the CLUB website."
  updated="April 19, 2026"
>
  <p>
    This page describes how the open-source CLUB project handles information
    collected through its public website. It applies only to this site —
    the pages served at this domain and their subpaths. It does not apply
    to CLUB instances that organizations run for themselves; each operator
    of a self-hosted CLUB instance publishes its own privacy notice, and
    that notice controls for users of that instance.
  </p>

  <h2>1. Who this is about</h2>
  <p>
    "CLUB," "the project," "we," and "us" refer to the maintainers and
    contributors of the open-source CLUB software. "You" refers to a
    visitor to this website. Source code, issues, and maintainer contact
    live in the project's public repository at
    <a href={GITHUB_URL}>GitHub</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>2. What the website collects</h2>
  <p>
    The CLUB website is a static marketing and documentation site. It is
    designed to be readable without accounts, cookies, or third-party
    scripts.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>No cookies.</strong> We do not set cookies from this site.
      Your browser is not asked to store anything identifying you.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>No analytics or telemetry.</strong> We do not run Google
      Analytics, Plausible, Fathom, Segment, or any equivalent service.
      No tracking pixels, heatmaps, or session recorders are embedded.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>No advertising.</strong> We do not serve ads and do not
      share data with ad networks.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>No user accounts.</strong> There is nothing to sign up for
      on this website, so no account, password, or profile is created.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. Information our host sees</h2>
  <p>
    This site is served through a static hosting provider and a content
    delivery network. Those providers automatically receive standard
    request data — your IP address, user-agent string, the URL you
    requested, and a timestamp — in order to deliver the page and to
    protect the service from abuse. That data is handled under the
    provider's own policy, is retained briefly in operational logs, and
    is not joined with any profile maintained by the CLUB project.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you install or update CLUB using the helper scripts hosted at
    <code>/install.sh</code> or <code>/uninstall.sh</code>, those
    requests are transparently proxied to the public source repository.
    They follow the same pattern as any other page request described
    above and are not tied to a user identity by us.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Outbound links</h2>
  <p>
    This site links to third-party destinations — primarily the project's
    GitHub repository, its documentation site, and the Dart and Flutter
    websites. When you follow such a link, the destination applies its
    own privacy practices. We have no visibility into what those
    services collect.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Children</h2>
  <p>
    CLUB is a developer tool. The website is not directed to children
    under 13 (or the equivalent minimum age in your jurisdiction) and we
    do not knowingly collect information from them.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Security</h2>
  <p>
    The site is served over HTTPS. Because no accounts or cookies exist,
    there is no personal dataset to breach on the website itself. If you
    believe you have found a security issue in the CLUB software,
    please report it through the project's public repository so it can
    be addressed for every deployment.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Changes to this notice</h2>
  <p>
    If this notice materially changes, the "Last updated" date at the top
    of this page will change, and the update will be reflected in the
    public source repository's history alongside the website content.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about this privacy notice — or about privacy on the CLUB
    software itself — can be filed as an issue in the project's public
    repository at <a href={GITHUB_URL}>GitHub</a>. Operators of
    individual CLUB instances handle questions about data stored on
    those instances.
  </p>

  <hr />

  <p class="eyebrow-inline">
    This notice covers the project's marketing site only. It is not the
    privacy policy of any particular CLUB deployment.
  </p>
</Legal>
